---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';

export function getStaticPaths() {
  const resources = {
    planning: {
      'project-timeline-planning': {
        title: 'Project Timeline Planning',
        content: `
# Project Timeline Planning

## Understanding Project Phases

Every construction project can be broken down into distinct phases:

1. Pre-Construction
   - Planning and design
   - Permits and approvals
   - Material sourcing
   
2. Construction
   - Site preparation
   - Foundation work
   - Framing
   - MEP installations
   - Interior/exterior finishes
   
3. Post-Construction
   - Final inspections
   - Punch list completion
   - Project closeout

## Creating Your Timeline

### 1. Define Project Scope
- List all required tasks
- Identify dependencies
- Set milestones

### 2. Estimate Durations
- Consider weather impacts
- Account for material lead times
- Include buffer for unexpected delays

### 3. Sequence Activities
- Use critical path method
- Identify parallel tasks
- Plan for resource availability

## Tips for Success

- Build in contingency time
- Update the timeline regularly
- Communicate changes to all stakeholders
- Track actual vs. planned progress
`
      },
      'budgeting-basics': {
        title: 'Budgeting Basics',
        content: `
# Construction Budgeting Basics

## Budget Components

### 1. Direct Costs
- Materials
- Labor
- Equipment rental
- Permits and fees

### 2. Indirect Costs
- Insurance
- Temporary facilities
- Project management
- Overhead

### 3. Contingency
- Recommended: 10-20% of total budget
- Higher for complex projects
- Account for market fluctuations

## Creating Your Budget

1. Research current material prices
2. Get multiple contractor quotes
3. Include permit fees
4. Factor in seasonal cost variations
5. Consider long-term maintenance costs

## Cost Control Strategies

- Track expenses in real-time
- Review and adjust regularly
- Document change orders
- Maintain detailed records
`
      },
      'material-estimation': {
        title: 'Material Estimation',
        content: `
# Material Estimation Guide

## Accurate Measurements

### Square Footage Calculation
- Measure room dimensions
- Account for windows and doors
- Include waste factor (10-15%)

### Volume Calculations
- Concrete requirements
- Fill materials
- Insulation needs

## Common Materials

### Lumber
- Board feet calculation
- Standard sizes
- Grade selection

### Drywall
- Sheet coverage
- Joint compound
- Tape and fasteners

### Flooring
- Room dimensions
- Pattern matching waste
- Underlayment requirements

## Tips for Accuracy

1. Double-check measurements
2. Include extra for mistakes
3. Consider material minimums
4. Account for shipping quantities
`
      }
    },
    design: {
      'space-planning': {
        title: 'Space Planning',
        content: `
# Space Planning Fundamentals

## Design Principles

### 1. Flow and Circulation
- Traffic patterns
- Room relationships
- Access points

### 2. Functionality
- Purpose-driven design
- Storage needs
- Future flexibility

### 3. Zoning
- Public vs. private spaces
- Quiet vs. active areas
- Work triangles

## Room-by-Room Considerations

### Kitchen
- Work triangle
- Counter space
- Storage requirements

### Living Areas
- Furniture placement
- Natural light
- Traffic flow

### Bedrooms
- Bed placement
- Closet access
- Privacy considerations

## Optimization Strategies

1. Multi-purpose spaces
2. Built-in storage
3. Natural light maximization
4. Future adaptability
`
      },
      'material-selection': {
        title: 'Material Selection',
        content: `
# Choosing the Right Materials

## Selection Criteria

### 1. Durability
- Expected lifespan
- Maintenance requirements
- Wear resistance

### 2. Aesthetics
- Color and texture
- Pattern options
- Finish choices

### 3. Cost Considerations
- Initial cost
- Installation expenses
- Long-term maintenance

## Common Materials

### Flooring
- Hardwood
- Tile
- Vinyl
- Carpet

### Countertops
- Granite
- Quartz
- Solid surface
- Laminate

### Wall Finishes
- Paint
- Wallpaper
- Tile
- Paneling

## Environmental Factors

1. Climate considerations
2. Sustainability
3. Indoor air quality
4. Energy efficiency
`
      },
      'design-principles': {
        title: 'Design Principles',
        content: `
# Construction Design Principles

## Core Principles

### 1. Balance
- Symmetrical vs. asymmetrical
- Visual weight
- Color harmony

### 2. Proportion
- Scale relationships
- Golden ratio
- Human scale

### 3. Unity
- Consistent elements
- Material harmony
- Color coordination

## Practical Application

### Room Design
- Focal points
- Furniture arrangement
- Lighting layers

### Exterior Design
- Curb appeal
- Material combinations
- Architectural style

### Color Theory
- Color schemes
- Light reflection
- Mood impact

## Implementation Tips

1. Start with function
2. Consider context
3. Plan for flexibility
4. Focus on details
`
      }
    },
    'tricks-of-the-trade': {
      'pro-tips': {
        title: 'Pro Tips',
        content: `
# Professional Construction Tips

## Planning Phase

### 1. Project Setup
- Create detailed checklists
- Document existing conditions
- Photograph before starting

### 2. Tool Preparation
- Maintain sharp blades
- Calibrate measuring tools
- Organize workspace

### 3. Material Handling
- Proper storage
- Acclimation periods
- Protection methods

## Execution Tips

### Measuring
- Measure twice, cut once
- Use story poles
- Mark reference lines

### Cutting
- Support materials properly
- Use appropriate blades
- Score before cutting

### Installation
- Level and plumb
- Proper spacing
- Clean as you go

## Problem Solving

1. Common issues
2. Quick fixes
3. When to call pros
`
      },
      'tool-guide': {
        title: 'Tool Guide',
        content: `
# Essential Construction Tools

## Hand Tools

### Measuring & Marking
- Tape measure
- Level
- Square
- Chalk line

### Cutting Tools
- Utility knife
- Hand saw
- Chisels
- Snips

### Assembly Tools
- Hammers
- Screwdrivers
- Pliers
- Wrenches

## Power Tools

### Essential Power Tools
- Drill/driver
- Circular saw
- Reciprocating saw
- Sander

### Specialty Tools
- Router
- Table saw
- Miter saw
- Air compressor

## Tool Care

1. Cleaning procedures
2. Storage methods
3. Maintenance schedule
4. Safety checks
`
      },
      'safety-first': {
        title: 'Safety First',
        content: `
# Construction Safety Guidelines

## Personal Protection

### 1. Safety Gear
- Eye protection
- Hearing protection
- Respiratory protection
- Work gloves

### 2. Proper Clothing
- Steel-toe boots
- Long pants
- Close-fitting clothes
- Hard hat when needed

## Tool Safety

### Power Tools
- Guard inspection
- Proper operation
- Maintenance checks
- Storage procedures

### Hand Tools
- Sharp blade safety
- Proper grip
- Tool condition
- Safe storage

## Site Safety

1. Clean workspace
2. Proper ventilation
3. Fire safety
4. First aid access

## Emergency Procedures

- First aid basics
- Emergency contacts
- Evacuation plans
- Accident reporting
`
      }
    }
  };

  return Object.entries(resources).flatMap(([category, items]) =>
    Object.entries(items).map(([slug, data]) => ({
      params: { category, slug },
      props: { data }
    }))
  );
}

const { category, slug } = Astro.params;
const { data } = Astro.props;
---

<Layout title={data.title}>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-12 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <nav class="mb-8">
      <a href="/resources" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-900">Resources</a>
      <span class="mx-2 text-primary-400">/</span>
      <a href={`/resources#${category}`} class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-900 capitalize">{category}</a>
      <span class="mx-2 text-primary-400">/</span>
      <span class="text-primary-900">{data.title}</span>
    </nav>

    <article class="prose prose-primary max-w-none">
      <div set:html={data.content} />
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>